        "title": "Java Enum: Encapsulation and runtime initialization",
        "body": "<p>I have a funny question on the way home<\/p>\n\n<p>I have an Enum<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public enum Gender{\n\n    Yes(Constants.male()), female(Constants.female());\n\n    private final String value;\n\n    private Gender(String option){\n          value = option;\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>.. should I encapsulate value or just declare it as public? <\/p>\n\n<p>Is there a disadvantage of run-time initializing the value?<\/p>\n",
