        "creation_date": 1362659868,
        "body": "<p>In your case there shouldn't be much difference, the <code>String<\/code> class is immutable. It is recommended however as encapsulation is good practice.<\/p>\n\n<p>As far as \"run-time\" init, I am not sure what you mean. Enum's as essentially singleton's so this would be inited when it is class-loaded. This is at runtime, yes, but there are no disadvantages; especially if you do not want to hardcode the values.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>As @GyroGearless points out the field should be declared as <code>final<\/code>, this is best practice even if it isn't <code>public<\/code> as it's a constant set in the constructor.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 15271451,
